            "id": "6843149cd203560001247687",
            "title": "Crude Oil Gains 2%; ABM Industries Shares Plunge After Q2 Results",
            "description": "<div><div class=\"sc-fLvBnq jggrSb\"><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">U.S. stocks traded higher midway through trading, with the Nasdaq Composite jumping more than 1% on Friday.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">The Dow traded up 1.05% to 42,765.32 while the NASDAQ gained 1.31% to 19,551.81. The S&amp;P 500 also rose, gaining, 1.10% to 6,004.74.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">Check This Out: <a href=\"https://www.benzinga.com/trading-ideas/long-ideas/25/06/45811726/cramer-says-hes-not-going-to-really-want-to-do-a-lot-of-china-right-now\" target=\"_blank\">Cramer Says He’s ‘Not Going To Really Want To Do A Lot Of China Right Now’</a></p><!--/$--><!--$--><!--$--><div class=\"sc-exeBjx kjPTmb raptive-ad-placement mx-auto overflow-hidden min-h-[250px] min-w-[300px] raptive-ad-wrapper flex flex-col items-center justify-center\"><div class=\"raptive-ben-content w-full flex items-center justify-center\" id=\"\"></div></div><!--/$--><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\"><strong>Leading and Lagging Sectors</strong><br/><br/>Energy shares jumped by 2% on Friday.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">In trading on Friday, utilities stocks fell by 0.2%.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\"><strong>Top Headline</strong></p><!--/$--><!--$--><div class=\"nativo-placement-in-content-ap\"></div><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">Shares of <strong>ABM Industries Inc.</strong> <span class=\"ticker\" data-exchange=\"NYSE\" data-ticker=\"ABM\" style=\"display:inline-block\">ABM</span> fell more than 13% on Friday after the company reported results for the second quarter.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">Revenue grew 4.6% year over year (Y/Y) to $2.11 billion, beating the consensus of $2.06 billion. This was led by organic growth of 3.8% and a 0.8% contribution from acquisitions. Adjusted EPS of 86 cents was in line with the consensus.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\">For FY25, ABM reiterated the adjusted EPS outlook at $3.65 to $3.80 versus the consensus of $3.77. The company continues to see an adjusted EBITDA margin of 6.3%- 6.5%.</p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\"><strong>Equities Trading UP<br/>           </strong></p><!--/$--><!--$--><ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Quanex Building Products Corporation </strong><span class=\"ticker\" data-exchange=\"NYSE\" data-ticker=\"NX\" style=\"display:inline-block\">NX</span> shares shot up 20% to $20.52 after the company reported better-than-expected second-quarter financial results.</li>\n<li>Shares of <strong>Davis Commodities Limited </strong><span class=\"ticker\" data-exchange=\"NASDAQ\" data-ticker=\"DTCK\" style=\"display:inline-block\">DTCK</span> got a boost, surging 50% to $0.9018 after the company announced approval of $30 million fundraising plan to establish Bitcoin reserves to strengthen asset allocation.</li>\n<li><strong>Venus Concept Inc. </strong><span class=\"ticker\" data-exchange=\"NASDAQ\" data-ticker=\"VERO\" style=\"display:inline-block\">VERO</span> shares were also up, gaining 17% to $2.80 after the company announced it entered into a definitive agreement to sell its Venus Hair business to Meta Healthcare Group.</li>\n</ul><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\"><strong>Equities Trading DOWN</strong></p><!--/$--><!--$--><p class=\"block core-block\"><strong>Latest Startup Investment Opportunities</strong>:</p><!--/$--><!--$--><div class=\"sc-ertdNE iHqtto block listing-preview-block\"><div class=\"sc-kuQJXd kRPBOC offerings-carousel-wrapper default GalleryCarousel_splide_slidewrap__zHpTC\"><div class=\"sc-iMAVTd gOePzW carousel-container\"><div aria-label=\"Carousel\" class=\"splide\"><div class=\"splide-track-wrapper\"><div class=\"splide__track\"><ul class=\"splide__list\"><li class=\"splide__slide\"><div class=\"sc-hgqGTP kxcIRr listing-preview default\"><div class=\"listing-image-container\"><a da